  Finding: `existsSync(guard.absolute)` does not distinguish `ENOENT` from other filesystem failures. For example, an inaccessible record can make `existsSync` return `false`, causing the reader to return `{ kind: "absent" }` and silently fall back to marker data. This violates the required “absent means ENOENT only” rule and AC6/AC9’s requirement that unreadable records be integrity faults.  
