  Finding: Record validation accepts malformed producer entries as valid. In particular, an unknown or non-string `parse_status` is silently converted to `null`, and a `not_run`/`not_applicable` entry with no valid `disposition` is accepted. This can render an invalid record as a normal completed/clean row or a non-run row without the reason mandated by AC3, rather than treating it as the schema-integrity fault required by AC6.  
